properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 4:44PM CST until February 17 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...Heavy Snow To Impact Travel Through the Evening...

.The slow moving system will produce snowfall rates of 1 to
2 inches per hour this afternoon and evening. A Winter Storm
Warning has been issued for Brown, Sibley, and Nicollet Counties,
which will see a couple more hours of heavy snow, and could have
localized 7 to 10 inches by the time the snow ends this evening.

Periods of snow, occasionally heavy at times, will spread across
south central, and east central Minnesota, and into west central
Wisconsin through the early evening. Snowfall amounts of 2 to 4
inches may be common across the advisory area, with localized
amounts of around 6 inches possible. The snow will end by 9 PM in
west central Wisconsin.

* WHAT...Snow. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches, with
localized amounts of up to around 6 inches possible.

* WHERE...In Wisconsin, St. Croix County. In Minnesota,
Hennepin, Ramsey, Washington and Carver Counties.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
